name: NBCNews
text:
More than 500 State Department employees have objected to being sent back to work in D.C. offices after an employee who works near Sec. Pompeo's office tested positive for the coronavirus.
https://t.co/0LtHzmsBXc

name: NBCNews
text: Children and staff at a Georgia overnight camp tested positive for COVID-19 after the camp did not require campers to wear face masks, the CDC says. https://t.co/qanaxuIydZ

name: NBCNews
text: WATCH: Morgan Freeman reads the words of John Lewis’ final essay, which he requested be published in the New York Times on the day of his funeral: “Together, You Can Redeem the Soul of Our Nation.” https://t.co/vf3sVIQHXH

name: NBCNews
text: Connie Culp, the first face transplant recipient in the US, has died, according to the Cleveland Clinic, which performed the surgery. https://t.co/plphn4y501

name: NBCNews
text:
President Trump's threatened TikTok ban could motivate young users to vote, some say.

“It kind of feels like our freedom of speech is being taken away,” says 18-year-old Anekha Singh. “Our ability to express ourselves is something he doesn’t want.” https://t.co/QRd957s8CJ

name: NBCNews
text: Factors such as testing delays, distrust and embarrassment are combining to make efforts to contain COVID-19 more difficult in the state that now has the highest number of cases in the nation. https://t.co/kaIjePirWz

name: NBCNews
text: Bryan Cranston reveals he has recovered from COVID-19: "I was pretty strict in adhering to the protocols and still... I contracted the virus." https://t.co/2UaFOatr2d
